There are many theories made known to the public about the causes of early puberty.
Yet there is no consistent theory that the hormones contained in milk or other foods, the chemicals present in the environment, or the sexual messages conveyed by the media are responsible.
Boys, like girls, reach puberty earlier.
Kaplowitz says the most credible hypothesis is the obesity epidemic.
He participated in a study of girls aged 6 to 9 years that linked the percentage of fat mass to the onset of puberty.
