However, his project, presented Thursday at a press conference in his native town of Aubervilliers, was born out of the desire to better defend multiculturalism, this great cultural melting pot that characterizes the neighborhoods above all.
My proposal n°1 is to create a ministry of multiculturalism, he says.
Abdel-Malik Djermoune, 50, a territorial attaché, today claims to be "100% apolitical" even if he has not always been neutral.
A 2002 campaigner alongside Jean-Pierre Chevénement, he then supported Dominique de Villepin locally between 2010 and 2011.
I know that the values of equality that I advocate in my program are linked to the left, but if the people on the right are willing to support me, I will listen to them too.
